##-> Allows clients on the external network to fetch emails from POP3 
##-> mail servers on the internal network. These rules are only enabled if
##-> Masquerading is disabled.
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @EXTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 110 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @EXTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 110 -d @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @INTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 110 -d @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @INTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 110 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A forward -i @INTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 110 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A forward -i @EXTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 110 -d @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
